<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880301-0072 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Central Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CTRL ADCO </CO><TEXT>   Central Corp. said it is discussing a possible joint venture or other business combination with Advantage Cos., Nashville, Tenn.    Fort Lauderdale, Fla.-based Central said the talks are non-binding and that no terms have been discussed. It said it agreed to allow Advantage to conduct a preliminary review of its operations.    Central provides long distance telephone operator systems for hotels and other businesses. Advantage is a publishing and telecommunications company.    In over-the-counter trading yesterday, Central shares were quoted at $4.75 bid. Advantage shares were quoted at $3.875 bid. </TEXT></DOC>